PGK is known to have ~7 such hydrophobic motifs that could potentially bind Hsp70, as shown in Fig 9. These binding sites were predicted using the limbo website, http://limbo. switchlab.org/limbo-analysis [48], which was developed for DnaK (bacterial Hsp70), but is still likely useful for other Hsp70s, although it may not properly identify all Hsp70 binding sites in

